name: Just For Fun: Ice Skating in San Jose
description:
A few friends and I are going ice skating at the Sharks Ice Arena in San Jose on Thursday at 7:30pm. It'd be great to see you if you wanted to join! Friends are welcome, and it's open skate so all experiences are welcome as well (they will even give you a stack of buckets to skate with if needed)

You are also welcome to join us for dinner beforehand, just let me know by 3pm day of so I can make it happen (reservations and whatnot, dinner location TBD) We will most likely be at the rink until 9:30! We will either have glow necklaces or Hawaiian leis--still undecided but I'll find a way of making us identifiable :D

Admission is $11.50, and you can rent skates for $5
The address for the ice skating rink is:

1500 South Tenth Street
San Jose, California 95112
how_to_find_us: Parking is super easy here, we will have either hawaiian leis or glow sticks so you can find us!

name: UX Networking Mixer Tuesday! (Light resume workshop)
description:
Come say hi and grab a drink or coffee, and meet other UX designers and aspiring UX designers! There is a bar and Starbucks coffee in the Hyatt and lots of nice lounge spots. Keri will be there to make introductions. Feel free to bring a friend!

I've added a theme that hopefully makes the gathering more beneficial to everyone: In case we run out of things to talk about, bring a resume and we'll take turns reviewing/making suggestions.

name: UX Portfolio Work Session
description:
This will be our first Portfolio Work Session so read on to know what to expect:

Please note that this is not a workshop. This is basically a study session to get work done on your portfolio by actually setting aside time to do it, but with friends who are in the same boat! This event is self-guided and work-at-your-own-pace, so come with your laptop and let this be your motivation to do the thing you kept telling yourself you'd work on "someday".

As this will be our first session, I expect we will have many questions (Where should I host? What should I include?). Please be open to discussing these questions as a group and possibly doing some Google-ing as a team to find out the answers. As we continue to do more of these, we can learn and be able to tell others what we found out, making these sessions more streamline and productive.

LOCATION:
We will be using the study room in the back of TOM N' TOMS coffee. As this room is limited in size, please keep your RSVPs updated.

Thursday (6PM-8PM) Tom N Toms Coffee
https://www.yelp.com/biz/tom-n-toms-coffee-santa-clara-3

name: UX-ology 101: Prototype with Adobe XD
description:
Hello there! We're going to be prototyping with Adobe XD. If you have little or no familiarity with prototyping with Adobe XD but were always curious, this is the session for you! Brian and Phi are going to walk you through two easy prototyping exercises using XD and Auto-animate, that will bring a lot of flexibility and style to your prototypes. Bring your laptops with Adobe XD installed (if you forget, we should have some time at the beginning to install, but save yourself some angst and come prepared if at all possible!) We'll do two quick prototyping demos, and answer any questions! Looking forward to seeing you!

We'll meet at 6pm, likely spend the first half hour getting settled in and start our prototyping at 6:30pm. We are expected to be done around 7 or 7:15 and will leave the rest of the hour up for questions and project work so you can put your new Auto Animate skills to good use!

PS This is the first in our UX-ology guided series. If you have a favorite tool that you'd like to see a demo on, please get in touch.

Keri

name: UXW Just For Fun - Day at the Park / PoGo Community Day
description:
Hey Wizards – Let’s get out and get some sun at the park! Pokémon Go is NOT required to join.

If you play Pokémon Go (app): It's Community Day, so come and catch some shiny Torchics together!

If you don’t play: come anyway and watch everyone at the park walk around with their phones out. (To be honest, it’s kind of fun to watch.)

Either way, we can all spend some healthy time outdoors, walk around, and be a little social with other UX Wizards. After the event (6pm) we may also grab some food someplace if people are interested.

FAMILY FRIENDLY EVENT: Friends, partners, or kids are welcome to join.

—

Location:
Central Park on Kiely Blvd.

Time:
3PM-6PM
Potentially dinner after 6PM
Come for all of it or just part of it!

What to bring (optional):
Water
Walking shoes
Snacks
Sunscreen
Umbrella
Jacket w/hood (weather says high of 61° & showers)
Phone with PoGo updated
Charging bricks for your phone

What to expect:
There is an event for the mobile game so expect the park to be busy with people walking slowly while looking at their phones. We can meet someplace initially and slow walk as a group or break up into small groups (whatever happens). We can chat about UX and go at our own pace, whether that means slow for those catching Pokémon or faster for those that come to exercise and socialize. If we’re lucky, we can also secure a picnic table for anyone that wants to rest and chat.

How to find us:
If you're unsure, keep an eye on the comment section.
> We'll meet at the bathrooms (near the Pavillion Area) beforehand and start walking once the event starts at 3PM.
> After 3PM, walk around the park and look for person(s) wearing a UX Wizards sign or wizard hat.
> If we decide to do food after, we will meet back up at the bathrooms beforehand.
how_to_find_us: See event description. Basically, keep an eye on the comments!

name: UX Career Alchemy | Headshots + Networking + Peer Review
description:
** NOTE: An RSVP on MeetUp does not count as registering. Please register via Eventbrite: http://bit.ly/2x2eRkg **

Hey Wizards – We would like to announce our very first UXWizards fundraiser! Turbocharge your career and get a professional headshot done for your LinkedIn (or website) by our very own Photographer Wizard Tammy. Bring your portfolio or resume and have it peer-reviewed, and enjoy some networking time that will also help support our group's future endeavors.

– Event Details –

Registration: $40 (All proceeds go to our MeetUp costs)

Sunday, June 30, 2019
Santana Row in San Jose, CA (Location specifics will be emailed to attendees 48 hours before the event)
Event 2pm-5pm PDT
Headshots 2pm-4pm PDT

– What To Expect –

Enjoy a fun casual event for chatting and networking with other UX designers or researchers! Come dressed and ready for your photo with our amazing photographer Tammy, and bring any work you'd like to get feedback on while you wait. There will be Wifi if you would like to bring your laptop to get advice on your portfolio, resume, or LinkedIn profile.

After the event, please allow for processing time for the photos. When ready, you will receive an email with 2-3 photos. See Example Headshots (https://photos.app.goo.gl/dmVM7CLpkUJpL4Tn6).

Space is limited, so please register on Eventbrite to guarantee your spot. Please note we will be closing RSVPs 48 hours before the event.

– Who Should Attend? –

Professionals looking for updated headshots, along with anyone who is curious about the industry, wants feedback or advice, or those in need of some inspiration to get ahead in their career! UXers (or aspiring UXers) of all levels are welcome.

– About The Photographer –

Tammy is a talented photographer in the SF Bay Area. She and her husband Mark started Memoire Studio (https://www.memoirestudio.com/) in 2008 and has experience photographing weddings, portrait sessions, and corporate events both locally and internationally.

– FAQ –

How can I Register?
Please register via Eventbrite: http://bit.ly/2x2eRkg

What is the refund policy?
There is no refund on tickets. We do allow ticket transfers for no additional costs.

How long do I have to Register?
You can Register as long as spots are available. Please be aware we will also be closing registration/RSVP for our event 48 hours before the event regardless of spots left.

How can I contact the organizer with any questions?
Please email us at [masked]

Will you be serving food or drink?
No, we will not be serving food or drink.

name: UX Portfolio Work Session
description:
Please note that this is not a workshop. This is basically a study session to get work done on your portfolio by actually setting aside time to do it, but with friends who are in the same boat! This event is self-guided and work-at-your-own-pace, so come with your laptop and let this be your motivation to do the thing you kept telling yourself you'd work on "someday".

We also take turns sharing and giving feedback on each others' portfolio and resumes, so this is a great way to get your worked checked and see what other people are doing.

LOCATION:
We will be using the Think Tank study room on the second floor of the Cupertino Library.

Friday (6PM-8PM) Cupertino Library Think Tank
https://www.sccl.org/Locations/Cupertino/About-Us/Meeting-Room/ThinkTank-Reservation-and-Usage-Policy

PLEASE NOTE there is a 15 person limit on the room and we cannot take more than that. We ask that you keep your RSVPs up to date.
how_to_find_us: Go up the stairs (or elevator) to the second floor. At the top of the stairs, turn sharp left and walk past the "Explore & Play" kiosk, past the women's restrooms, and continue down the rust-colored wall. The room is halfway down on the right.

name: UX Wizards Book Club: The Design of Everyday Things - Chapter 1
description:
— Welcome to our first UX Wizards Book Club meeting! —

For our first book we’ll be reading The Design of Everyday Things by Don Norman on Thursday nights in September. We’ll be discussing about 2 chapters a week (see tentative schedule at the bottom).

John Brewer will lead the reading group in the style described in this document: http://www.industriallogic.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/khdraft1.pdf

Meetup is held at Star Space in Sunnyvale.
https://www.yelp.com/biz/star-space-sunnyvale

*** As we have limited space, please only RSVP if you are serious about attending and come prepared to discuss the material. ***

--------------------------------------------

— The Design of Everyday Things by Don Norman —

https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/840.The_Design_of_Everyday_Things

"Anyone who designs anything to be used by humans -- from physical objects to computer programs to conceptual tools -- must read this book, and it is an equally tremendous read for anyone who has to use anything created by another human. It could forever change how you experience and interact with your physical surroundings, open your eyes to the perversity of bad design and the desirability of good design, and raise your expectations about how things should be designed."

--------------------------------------------

— Reading Schedule —
The following chapters will be discussed on these dates:

September 5
Introductions and Overview
Chapter 1 - The Psychopathology of Everyday Things

September 12
Chapter 2 - The Psychology of Everyday Actions
Chapter 3 - Knowledge in the Head and in the World

September 19
Chapter 4 - Knowing What to Do: Constraints Discoverability, and Feedback
Chapter 5 - Human Error? No, Bad Design

September 26
Chapter 6 - Design Thinking
Chapter 7 - Design in the World of Business

name: UX Chicken
description:
We're moving out of the digital world to investigate what makes a good fried chicken user experience.

Potential discussion items include
TOOLING: When you have to work while you eat and can't eat with your hands, what is the tool of choice? Forks? Chopsticks?
DESIGN LANGUAGE: What should be the proper set of cold dishes for fried chicken?
SKEUOMORPHISM: Unlike a thanksgiving turkey, fried chicken rarely comes as one giant bird, but should it be? Is there anything of value not in the drumsticks or wings?
RESPONSIVE: Given the wide variety of spiciness and flavors, what's the right recipe for all tummies?

name: Designers Meet! - Meetaway
description:
This online speed networking event is for UX, Product & Graphic Designers who are looking to make valuable connections with peers all around the world.

Resgister Here: https://meetaway.com/event/1571700117166x375764004987207700

WHAT IS IT?
Design works best when it's collective, so come along and share your story with others and contribute to the discussion. In our first ever Meetaway, you will have the chance to match with at least 7 designers around the world for 10 minutes each.

HOW DOES IT WORK?
Meetaways are online events that intelligently match attendees for a series of 1-on-1 video calls. After each conversation, attendees automatically rotate to the next one. You just log in to the event and Meetaway will handle the rest.

WHY SHOULD I JOIN?
Whether you are looking for your next job, exploring other companies, like brainstorming with others like you or you are just a beginner, this event is for you! Do not worry about your level of expertise, everyone has a story to tell.

WHAT DO I NEED TO ATTEND?
Laptop or desktop with Chrome or Firefox. Meetaway does not support mobile devices because the screen movements are often distracting and having everyone on a laptop or desktop results in a better overall experience for everyone.

WHO ARE WE?
We are UX Wizards of the South Bay, a designer community-based in the SF Bay Area. We are expanding our reach every day through meetups, events, workshops and online gatherings. More information available from the link below.
https://www.meetup.com/UX-WIZARDS-OF-THE-SOUTH-BAY/

Let's do this!

name: Designers Meet! - Meetaway
description:
*THIS IS AN ONLINE EVENT*

This online speed networking event is for UX, Product & Graphic Designers who are looking to make valuable connections with peers all around the world.

ONLINE Register Here:
https://meetaway.com/event/1580255065305x693247657375957000

WHAT IS IT?
Design works best when it's collective, so come along and share your story with others and contribute to the discussion. In our first ever Meetaway, you will have the chance to match with at least 7 designers around the world for 10 minutes each.

HOW DOES IT WORK?
Meetaways are online events that intelligently match attendees for a series of 1-on-1 video calls. After each conversation, attendees automatically rotate to the next one. You just log in to the event and Meetaway will handle the rest.

WHY SHOULD I JOIN?
Whether you are looking for your next job, exploring other companies, like brainstorming with others like you or you are just a beginner, this event is for you! Do not worry about your level of expertise, everyone has a story to tell.

WHAT DO I NEED TO ATTEND?
Laptop or desktop with Chrome or Firefox. Meetaway does not support mobile devices because the screen movements are often distracting and having everyone on a laptop or desktop results in a better overall experience for everyone.

WHO ARE WE?
We are UX Wizards of the South Bay, a designer community-based in the SF Bay Area. We are expanding our reach every day through meetups, events, workshops and online gatherings. More information available from the link below.
https://www.meetup.com/UX-WIZARDS-OF-THE-SOUTH-BAY/

6:30pm - Whole group gathers, intros & quick hello
6:50pm - Break into smaller groups for Session 1 (you can choose from topics A, B or C)
7:10pm - Return to large room with whole group
7:20pm - Break into smaller groups for Session 2 (you can choose from topics D, E or F)
7:40pm/8:00pm - Event ends (wiggle room for running late)

We have a few topics we've chosen, and we are also open to suggestions for additional topics:

Topic B: UX Researcher Chat (a place for researchers or the research-inclined)
